OL,6,FMark's widow Helen has been driving
OL,7,Fthe support van and watching her kids
OL,8,Ftake on the challenge
OL,10,FHis symptoms progressed quickly- he
OL,11,Fwas 24 hours on a breathing machine
OL,12,Fand became weaker in his limbs so it
OL,13,Fbecame more and more difficult to walk.
OL,15,FMND affects almost 5000 people in the
OL,16,FUK at any one time.
OL,18,FMotor neurones are the nerves in the
OL,19,Fbrain and spinal cord which carry
OL,20,Fmessages to the muscles telling them
OL,21,Fwhat to do.
